title: YUM/DNF Update Check
agents: linux
author: Henri Wahl <h.wahl@ifw-dresden.de>
catalog: os/updates
license: GPL
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors available package updates via {yum} or {dnf}
 on Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8-10 and compatible RPM-based distributions
 (AlmaLinux, Rocky Linux, Oracle Linux, CentOS Stream).

 The agent plugin detects the appropriate package manager ({dnf5}, {dnf},
 or {yum}) and reports the number of pending normal and security updates,
 the timestamp of the last applied update, and whether a reboot is required
 due to a kernel update.

 Thresholds for normal and security update counts as well as the maximum
 age of the last update can be configured via WATO rules.

 The check goes {CRIT} by default if a reboot is required after a kernel
 update. This state can be overridden via a WATO rule.

 The plugin must be deployed to the agent's {plugins} directory, either
 manually or through the Agent Bakery.

inventory:
 One service {YUM Updates} is created for each host where the {yum} agent
 plugin produces output.
